  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Enjoy your meals with a view at the Panorama Restaurant. On half board you'll have your breakfast and dinner here on the first floor with views towards the <span>Silvretta glacier</span>. Breakfast is buffet style and includes freshly baked, crispy bread from the local bakery and milk from the Davos dairy, as well as some hot options. In the evening you'll have a three course buffet dinner or three course menu with choice of main. The chef uses local products where possible, but serves up tasty dishes from around the world.</p>
<p>Stübli Restaurant is the hotel's a la carte option (payable locally). It's open for coffees, lunch and dinner - this is the place to head for some authentic Swiss style, cosy, casual atmosphere, with local and regional specialities like fondue and raclette. Open from 9am-11pm daily.  </p>
<p>Catch up with friends after a day on the slopes in the Piano Bar, where you'll find live music and a great selection of drinks. </p>
<p>If you're celebrating Christmas at the Silvretta Park you'll have a gala dinner included, with carol singing and forest Christmas celebrations. New Year gala dinner with a buffet, entertainment and a DJ is also included. </p>
<p>Early meal times for children are available on request. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
