  <description><![CDATA[<p>In a quiet location, close to the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/b23ef1df250240c5a3657f721fdb96d0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b23ef1df250240c5a3657f721fdb96d0}" title="Klosters">Klosters</a> Platz, the Silvretta Park is a beautiful family-run hotel furnished in an Alpine-style throughout. </p>
<h2>Swiss hospitality</h2>
<p>The Silvretta Park opened it's doors to its first guests over 150 years years ago, so they are well versed in hospitality. The hotel benefits from a range of excellent facilities including comfortable rooms, indoor pool, wellness facilities, an excellent half board restaurant, piano bar and saloon lounge. It has a lovely relaxed atmosphere and is an ideal base for family groups, couples and solo travellers. </p>
<h2>Silvretta Glacier views</h2>
<p>One of our favourite things about the location of the Silvretta Park is the view you get from the Panorama Restaurant over the glacier. In addition to that, the Gotschna cable-car for access to the main ski area, is just 400 metres away and the bus stop for the Madrisa ski area is around the corner. </p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>Located on the first floor, with views towards the Silvretta glacier, you will have breakfast and dinner in the Panorama Restaurant. The breakfast buffet features various hot and cold options, as well as freshly made bread from the local bakery and milk from the Davos dairy. In the evening, you will have a three-course dinner buffet or a three-course dinner menu with choice of main. The chef prioritises using regional ingredients wherever possible, but prepares delicious meals from all over the world.</p>]]></description>
